verbose_text: Interestingly, larvae reared at this level had greater growth and survival and greater percentage metamorphosis, than larvae reared at both the present day CO 2 level (390 ppm) and at the elevated CO 2 (1,500 ppm) level, indicating that either ocean acidification is already impacting larvae of mollusc species [XREF_BIBR] or adaptation to present conditions has occurred.
